WEBVTT

00:01.468 --> 00:02.868
Hey, what's up, Trey?

00:02.870 --> 00:04.803
I got a bunch of assholes
renting a house next to me.

00:04.805 --> 00:06.539
People come from out of town,
they move here,

00:06.541 --> 00:08.473
and just make life shitty
for the rest of us.

00:08.475 --> 00:09.808
[ Glass breaking, man groans ]

00:09.810 --> 00:11.877
If I even see either of you
in Oceanside again,

00:11.879 --> 00:13.546
we're gonna have some
real issues, alright?

00:13.548 --> 00:16.549
Why didn't you come help me
pull up the tiles at the bar?

00:16.551 --> 00:17.816
Trying to
avoid bars right now.

00:17.818 --> 00:19.418
Still doing
the sober thing, huh?

00:19.420 --> 00:20.753
Still doing
the sober thing.

00:20.755 --> 00:22.021
What were you doing
this morning?

00:22.023 --> 00:23.356
I was at the lot.

00:23.358 --> 00:24.890
Man: It's not much use to us
just sitting there.

00:24.892 --> 00:26.491
Man: I think it's my lot,
and I'm gonna do with it

00:26.493 --> 00:29.562
what I want when I want.

00:29.564 --> 00:31.830
Man: He attacked two people
with a skateboard,

00:31.832 --> 00:34.633
sent one to the hospital.
-He was protecting himself

00:34.635 --> 00:36.435
and his sister.
-The school thinks they were

00:36.437 --> 00:38.037
involved in the theft
of computers.

00:38.039 --> 00:40.839
Woman: I think what happened
here over the weekend

00:40.841 --> 00:43.442
is a symptom of a larger problem
with Julia.

00:43.444 --> 00:45.711
[ Laughs ]
Oh, my God!

00:45.713 --> 00:46.979
Julia!

00:46.981 --> 00:49.314
You know, I went
to your school today.

00:49.316 --> 00:51.850
You're getting expelled.
What?

00:51.852 --> 00:54.053
There just wasn't anything
I could do.

00:54.055 --> 00:58.791
♪♪

00:58.793 --> 01:04.663
♪ She stares deeply ♪

01:04.665 --> 01:09.001
♪ Locked inside me ♪

01:09.003 --> 01:14.673
♪ Burnin' brightly ♪

01:14.675 --> 01:20.746
♪ One they know
that I cannot take ♪

01:20.748 --> 01:24.417
♪ Waitin' for it all to begin ♪

01:24.419 --> 01:29.222
♪ Every night now, they'll win ♪

01:31.492 --> 01:33.626
♪ Come and meet my black hole ♪

01:33.628 --> 01:36.695
♪ Got a big black hole ♪

01:36.697 --> 01:40.433
♪ Got a big
black hole ♪

01:40.435 --> 01:46.038
♪ I've got a big black hole ♪

01:46.040 --> 01:49.241
♪ I've got a big black,
big black hole ♪

01:49.243 --> 01:53.712
♪ Got a big black hole
inside of me ♪

01:53.714 --> 02:01.253
♪♪

02:01.255 --> 02:08.594
♪♪

02:08.596 --> 02:16.201
♪♪

02:16.203 --> 02:23.542
♪♪

02:23.544 --> 02:31.050
♪♪

02:36.291 --> 02:40.927
[ Water splashing ]

02:47.635 --> 02:49.902
Party favors
are up, ladies.

02:49.904 --> 02:53.372
-Bro.
-Bro!

02:53.374 --> 02:54.373
Bro, relax, man.

02:54.375 --> 02:55.908
I remember
where you hid the key.

02:55.910 --> 02:57.843
Yo, you know how lucky you are
I didn't have a gun on me?

02:57.845 --> 02:59.578
It's your lucky day,
not mine, brother.

02:59.580 --> 03:01.446
Oh?
Why's that?

03:01.448 --> 03:03.582
Maya, Sandy.

03:03.584 --> 03:05.184
[ Giggling ]

03:05.186 --> 03:06.785
Okay.

03:06.787 --> 03:09.322
This is my boy Craig
I was tellin' you 'bout.

03:09.324 --> 03:10.990
Hi.
Hi.

03:10.992 --> 03:13.192
Thanks for letting us
use your shower.

03:13.194 --> 03:14.593
Yeah.

03:14.595 --> 03:18.197
[ Sniffing ]

03:18.199 --> 03:19.999
Bro, I'm gonna
need you to leave.

03:20.001 --> 03:23.202
I figured if I brought some
friends, you'd change your mind.

03:23.204 --> 03:25.204
Yeah, but I told you
I cleaned up.

03:25.206 --> 03:27.806
Nice tats.

03:27.808 --> 03:31.777
Dude, one day of fun
ain't gonna kill you.

03:33.748 --> 03:36.081
You know, you're kind
of embarrassing me.

03:36.083 --> 03:43.556
♪♪

03:43.558 --> 03:45.691
Well, then you leave...

03:45.693 --> 03:48.493
and they stay.

03:48.495 --> 03:49.494
What?

03:49.496 --> 03:51.564
You leave...

03:51.566 --> 03:53.966
and they stay.

03:53.968 --> 03:56.635
Bro, are you serious?

03:56.637 --> 03:58.237
Yeah.

04:00.041 --> 04:02.841
Alright, so what
were your names again?

04:02.843 --> 04:04.509
Bro!
[ Scoffs ]

04:04.511 --> 04:06.511
♪♪

04:06.513 --> 04:08.181
[ Sighs ]

04:09.717 --> 04:14.053
[ Cellphone vibrating ]

04:14.055 --> 04:15.254
Hello?

04:15.256 --> 04:17.390
<i> -Woman: Joshua Cody?</i>
-Yeah.

04:17.392 --> 04:19.592
<i> This is Lana from Niemann,</i>
<i> Livingston, and Kohl.</i>

04:19.594 --> 04:21.526
<i> I'm returning your call</i>
<i> regarding scheduling</i>

04:21.528 --> 04:23.262
<i> an initial consultation.</i>

04:23.264 --> 04:25.464
That's right -- uh, thanks for
calling me back.

04:25.466 --> 04:27.666
<i> Of course --</i>
<i> would you be available</i>

04:27.668 --> 04:29.001
<i> to come in sometime today?</i>

04:29.003 --> 04:30.803
-I would.
<i> -Great.</i>

04:30.805 --> 04:33.272
<i> Hold for a second</i>
<i> while I pull up my calendar.</i>

04:33.274 --> 04:38.611
♪♪

04:38.613 --> 04:44.149
♪♪

04:44.151 --> 04:47.686
Mornin'.

04:47.688 --> 04:49.021
You have fun out there?

04:49.023 --> 04:50.990
Yeah, it was great.

04:54.495 --> 04:56.695
It's pretty impressive.

04:56.697 --> 04:58.497
I'm a little rusty.

04:58.499 --> 05:01.366
Can still make some turns
on it, though.

05:01.368 --> 05:04.703
Yeah, I wasn't talking
about the surfing.

05:04.705 --> 05:05.971
Ah.

05:05.973 --> 05:07.506
So, fourth date.

05:07.508 --> 05:09.374
Gotta ask --

05:09.376 --> 05:12.111
how does the owner of a dive bar
afford a place like this?

05:15.716 --> 05:18.517
Frozen taquitos.

05:18.519 --> 05:20.653
Water down the booze.

05:20.655 --> 05:22.255
Got it, got it.

05:22.257 --> 05:25.991
We're gonna keep doing the whole
sexy/mysterious thing.

05:25.993 --> 05:28.261
If you want me to, sure.

05:28.263 --> 05:29.995
Oh, yeah, here,
let me help you with that.

05:29.997 --> 05:31.530
Huh.
Sorry.

05:31.532 --> 05:32.531
Can't really help myself.

05:32.533 --> 05:33.532
Anybody home?!

05:33.534 --> 05:34.800
Hey!
Oh, shit.

05:34.802 --> 05:36.201
Hey.
Hey.

05:36.203 --> 05:38.337
Hey, sorry.
Okay if I come down?

05:38.339 --> 05:39.538
Yeah, yeah.

05:39.540 --> 05:41.274
I went by the bar,
but it was closed,

05:41.276 --> 05:43.476
and, uh, I'm heading down to
Baja Malibu

05:43.478 --> 05:45.744
for a couple of days,
I wanted to drop this off

05:45.746 --> 05:48.681
before I left.

05:48.683 --> 05:49.948
For me?

05:49.950 --> 05:51.350
'76 Lightning Bolt.

05:51.352 --> 05:53.619
First board I ever made
for Hawaiian waves.

05:53.621 --> 05:55.954
Fully restored.

05:55.956 --> 05:57.222
You shitting me?

05:57.224 --> 05:58.291
No.
It's yours.

05:58.293 --> 06:00.359
Oh, my God, man.
Thank you.

06:00.361 --> 06:01.894
That one you can hang
on the wall.

06:01.896 --> 06:03.762
Hell yeah, I will.

06:03.764 --> 06:06.365
Beautiful, man.

06:06.367 --> 06:08.633
Holy shit.

06:08.635 --> 06:11.904
It's good to have somebody
looking out for us locals again

06:11.906 --> 06:15.040
with your mom gone.

06:15.042 --> 06:17.310
Yeah.
'Course.

06:17.312 --> 06:18.844
Thank you.

06:18.846 --> 06:21.113
Thank you, Trey.
Thank you.

06:21.115 --> 06:23.248
Hey, have a good one.

06:23.250 --> 06:24.650
You too.

06:24.652 --> 06:26.652
Put it up tonight.
Yeah!

06:26.654 --> 06:28.287
Yes, sir!

06:31.326 --> 06:33.258
What happened
with your mom?

06:33.260 --> 06:36.529
♪♪

06:36.531 --> 06:38.397
Nothin'.

06:38.399 --> 06:46.772
♪♪

07:03.824 --> 07:05.424
Excuse me.

07:05.426 --> 07:08.027
I'm looking for
the property owner?

07:08.029 --> 07:09.494
That's me.

07:09.496 --> 07:10.963
Oh, okay.

07:10.965 --> 07:13.298
Marc Landreau,
Coastal Visions Realty.

07:13.300 --> 07:15.134
Mind if
I take a look around?

07:17.172 --> 07:19.171
It's not for sale, so...

07:19.173 --> 07:21.440
Well, it's listed, so...

07:21.442 --> 07:22.708
What?

07:22.710 --> 07:24.910
Most of my clients
are investment groups.

07:24.912 --> 07:26.245
They do
a lot of cash deals.

07:26.247 --> 07:29.382
There's got to be
a mistake.

07:29.384 --> 07:31.850
I-I have the listing
right here.

07:31.852 --> 07:33.452
That's my phone.

07:35.390 --> 07:38.391
It has Josh Cody
as the listing agent.

07:38.393 --> 07:42.327
♪♪

07:42.329 --> 07:43.929
[ Scoffs ]

07:43.931 --> 07:45.565
It's not for sale!

07:48.002 --> 07:50.335
It's not for sale!
Okay.

07:50.337 --> 07:58.411
♪♪

07:58.413 --> 07:59.879
Shit!

07:59.881 --> 08:03.548
[ Skateboard rolling ]

08:03.550 --> 08:04.617
Nice.

08:04.619 --> 08:06.351
Can't do 'em every time yet.

08:06.353 --> 08:07.887
Hey, hang out
with me today.

08:07.889 --> 08:10.355
I need to find a job.

08:10.357 --> 08:12.091
I can't.

08:12.093 --> 08:15.261
I got to go meet some lawyer
Smurf found.

08:19.233 --> 08:21.166
Are you worried?

08:21.168 --> 08:23.502
About what?

08:23.504 --> 08:24.770
Juvie, Andrew.

08:24.772 --> 08:27.840
[ Sighs ]
Smurf said she's gonna fix it.

08:27.842 --> 08:29.908
And you believe her?

08:29.910 --> 08:32.511
Andrew, you're supposed
to be getting ready.

08:32.513 --> 08:34.246
You know I don't like
to be late.

08:34.248 --> 08:37.650
And don't ride that
goddamn thing near my car!

08:42.590 --> 08:44.657
Oh, Julia.

08:52.199 --> 08:53.398
You're staying home
today, baby.

08:53.400 --> 08:56.269
I need you to watch
Craig and Deran.

08:56.271 --> 08:58.403
Baz can watch them.
Mnh-mnh.

08:58.405 --> 08:59.605
I have plans.

08:59.607 --> 09:03.208
Baz is actually doing
something for me today.

09:03.210 --> 09:05.344
[ Scoffs ]
Right.

09:05.346 --> 09:08.080
Guess that's all any of us
get to do, huh.

09:10.217 --> 09:12.185
[ Skateboard clatters ]

09:15.422 --> 09:19.892
Just try not to be high all day
with your face in a book, baby.

09:19.894 --> 09:23.696
Put that stupid thing away
and go get cleaned up.

09:23.698 --> 09:25.431
You got 10 minutes.

09:28.970 --> 09:31.236
Thanks for
having my back.

09:31.238 --> 09:33.372
Jesus, Andrew.

09:33.374 --> 09:42.982
♪♪

09:42.984 --> 09:52.391
♪♪

09:52.393 --> 09:54.527
[ Skateboard clatters ]

09:54.529 --> 10:03.402
♪♪

10:03.404 --> 10:12.144
♪♪

10:12.146 --> 10:14.947
[ Vehicle approaches ]

10:14.949 --> 10:20.019
♪♪

10:20.021 --> 10:22.421
The hell do you think
you're doin'?

10:22.423 --> 10:25.691
What are you talkin' about?
I'm talkin' about my lot.

10:25.693 --> 10:28.293
My lot! You're sellin' my lot
out from underneath me?!

10:28.295 --> 10:30.095
No.
Bullshit!

10:30.097 --> 10:31.096
Pope --
It's listed! It's my lot!

10:31.098 --> 10:32.164
Pope, relax.
You listed my lot!

10:32.166 --> 10:33.832
Relax, relax.

10:33.834 --> 10:35.034
Okay?

10:35.036 --> 10:37.636
I just wanted to see what comps
we could get for the area,

10:37.638 --> 10:38.971
see what it's worth to us
on the market.

10:38.973 --> 10:40.105
That's all.

10:40.107 --> 10:42.441
That's all.

10:42.443 --> 10:45.510
Look, I can't sell shit
until you sign off on it first.

10:45.512 --> 10:48.381
Alright? It's not goin'
anywhere, it's yours.

10:52.453 --> 10:53.986
You take it down.

10:53.988 --> 10:55.721
Fine.
Today.

10:55.723 --> 10:57.856
Yes.

10:57.858 --> 10:59.525
Jesus Christ, man.

11:03.731 --> 11:05.931
I just wanted to see what you
were doin' out there, man.

11:05.933 --> 11:08.267
I --
It's been three months.

11:12.473 --> 11:15.208
Look, I want to text everyone
for a meeting today.

11:15.210 --> 11:18.010
I want to go over
the businesses, jobs,

11:18.012 --> 11:19.212
properties, everything.

11:19.214 --> 11:21.214
I wanna keep everything
out in the open.

11:21.216 --> 11:23.482
Take the listing down.

11:23.484 --> 11:25.084
Move your truck.

11:25.086 --> 11:28.153
♪♪

11:28.155 --> 11:31.123
[ Starts engine ]

11:34.963 --> 11:36.462
To your right, to your right.
Alright.

11:36.464 --> 11:37.996
Line it up with this tap.
This one.

11:37.998 --> 11:39.197
Just take your time.
It's not heavy at all.

11:39.199 --> 11:40.466
Drop this shit,
I'm gonna kill you.

11:40.468 --> 11:42.401
Here.
Boom, perfect.

11:42.403 --> 11:43.535
Right there?
Yep.

11:43.537 --> 11:45.471
I would never drop this.

11:45.473 --> 11:46.873
Yo.
What's up, man?

11:46.875 --> 11:48.607
Check out this new addition.

11:48.609 --> 11:50.008
'76 Bolt.

11:50.010 --> 11:51.410
Believe this shit?
Great.

11:51.412 --> 11:53.479
Can we talk?

11:53.481 --> 11:55.013
Outside?

11:55.015 --> 11:57.950
Yeah.

11:57.952 --> 11:59.752
Um...

11:59.754 --> 12:02.421
I need a favor.

12:02.423 --> 12:04.090
Okay.

12:05.960 --> 12:07.960
Will you swap houses
with me?

12:07.962 --> 12:09.962
What?

12:09.964 --> 12:11.764
Yeah, will you swap houses
with me?

12:11.766 --> 12:14.633
I mean, that place is
perfect for you, man.

12:14.635 --> 12:15.902
You got the waves outside,
it's --

12:15.904 --> 12:19.438
Yeah, I got waves out
in front of my house, too.

12:19.440 --> 12:22.308
Yeah, man, but I --
I can't stay there.

12:22.310 --> 12:26.445
Alright? It's like a conveyor
belt of women and coke, and...

12:26.447 --> 12:27.846
I don't know.
If I do, I just feel like

12:27.848 --> 12:29.715
I'm gonna go back
into the partying and...

12:29.717 --> 12:31.450
I don't know.
Board up the windows.

12:31.452 --> 12:33.252
Get new locks on the door.
What do you want me to do?

12:33.254 --> 12:35.654
Bro, I'm being serious.
Yeah, me too, man.

12:35.656 --> 12:39.325
I don't want to move out
of my house.

12:39.327 --> 12:42.528
I need this.

12:42.530 --> 12:46.132
Uh, no.

12:46.134 --> 12:48.066
♪♪

12:48.068 --> 12:50.068
You know what?
Thanks for nothing, man.

12:50.070 --> 12:51.137
It's always the same.

12:51.139 --> 12:52.538
You're not asking me for a ride.

12:52.540 --> 12:53.872
I don't want to help.
It's great.

12:53.874 --> 12:56.275
You're asking me to move
out of my house.

12:56.277 --> 13:04.683
♪♪

13:04.685 --> 13:13.091
♪♪

13:13.093 --> 13:21.500
♪♪

13:21.502 --> 13:22.568
Janine Cody?

13:22.570 --> 13:24.170
That's right.
Morgan Wilson.

13:24.172 --> 13:25.972
Pleasure.

13:25.974 --> 13:27.306
You must be Andrew.

13:27.308 --> 13:28.374
Nice to meet you.

13:28.376 --> 13:30.076
Come on back.

13:33.381 --> 13:35.081
Have a seat.

13:36.917 --> 13:39.251
Oh, uh...
Pardon me.

13:39.253 --> 13:41.287
Let me get that
out of the way.

13:48.796 --> 13:51.864
So, the charge is juvenile
assault and battery.

13:51.866 --> 13:53.866
Usually not a big deal
for a first offense,

13:53.868 --> 13:57.069
but it was on
state property,

13:57.071 --> 14:00.640
and it was against
a state employee.

14:05.746 --> 14:08.280
To complicate things,
there was a burglary

14:08.282 --> 14:10.148
and theft
at the school that day.

14:10.150 --> 14:12.284
Which Andrew had nothing
to do with.

14:12.286 --> 14:14.753
And he was defending
his sister.

14:14.755 --> 14:16.689
I'm sure.

14:16.691 --> 14:20.193
But any half-decent juvenile
prosecutor will bring it up.

14:22.030 --> 14:25.698
It's important to demonstrate
good-faith efforts

14:25.700 --> 14:29.568
to address Andrew's behavior
prior to your hearing.

14:29.570 --> 14:31.704
I suggest making an appointment
for Andrew

14:31.706 --> 14:33.973
to speak
to a psychiatrist.

14:38.312 --> 14:41.214
Andrew, why don't you
wait outside.

14:43.317 --> 14:44.984
Thank you, baby.

14:55.796 --> 14:59.932
I have no problem
with what my son did.

14:59.934 --> 15:02.334
I came here because

15:02.336 --> 15:06.405
you come
highly recommended.

15:06.407 --> 15:08.807
By whom?

15:08.809 --> 15:10.443
Angel Cordero.

15:14.282 --> 15:15.882
How is Angel?

15:19.153 --> 15:23.689
He's free as a bird,
thanks to you.

15:23.691 --> 15:26.358
I'll tell him you asked.

15:26.360 --> 15:28.160
So...

15:28.162 --> 15:29.962
what I'm looking for...

15:32.232 --> 15:36.168
is the Angel Cordero package.

15:36.170 --> 15:38.904
Not the "concerned mother,
trying to save her wayward son"

15:38.906 --> 15:41.774
package.

15:41.776 --> 15:44.944
That package costs more.

15:47.381 --> 15:48.514
'Course.

15:48.516 --> 15:54.520
♪♪

15:54.522 --> 16:00.793
♪♪

16:00.795 --> 16:03.930
Are you hungry?

16:03.932 --> 16:06.799
Want to go get a burger?

16:09.804 --> 16:11.871
Don't you want to know
how it went?

16:18.947 --> 16:21.347
Am I gonna have to talk
to a psychiatrist?

16:21.349 --> 16:22.949
No.

16:24.953 --> 16:26.685
It's okay.

16:26.687 --> 16:28.420
I mean, if I have to,
it's better than juvie.

16:28.422 --> 16:30.957
Do you want to?

16:30.959 --> 16:32.891
No, but the lawyer said --

16:32.893 --> 16:34.527
Forget what she said.

16:41.035 --> 16:43.336
You don't talk to anybody ever.

16:46.841 --> 16:48.507
I know.

16:48.509 --> 16:51.177
♪♪

16:53.581 --> 16:55.447
Where you been?

16:55.449 --> 16:57.916
Working.

16:57.918 --> 16:59.451
On what?

16:59.453 --> 17:01.854
Let's get this shit over with.
I got stuff to do.

17:01.856 --> 17:04.891
-Should we go sit down?
-No, let's get it over with.

17:06.794 --> 17:09.195
Okay.

17:09.197 --> 17:11.998
Alright, sales on Smurf's
properties, uh,

17:12.000 --> 17:14.266
her apartments,
they're almost done.

17:14.268 --> 17:16.802
Just a couple stragglers
in a few places

17:16.804 --> 17:19.338
that we got to kick out.

17:19.340 --> 17:23.809
Then all we'll have left
are the houses and Pope's lot.

17:23.811 --> 17:27.145
We're also sitting on a ton
of money, but it's all dirty.

17:27.147 --> 17:29.281
I can wash some of it
through the property sales,

17:29.283 --> 17:31.350
but the rest is gonna have
to go through the, uh,

17:31.352 --> 17:34.053
existing businesses
until we get new ones.

17:36.024 --> 17:39.291
I also want to hire
a new attorney.

17:39.293 --> 17:40.693
We need to start fresh,

17:40.695 --> 17:42.628
cut whatever ties
with anyone we had before.

17:42.630 --> 17:45.431
Okay, why do we need to have
a lawyer on retainer?

17:45.433 --> 17:47.299
I mean, everything you've been
doing yourself has been fine.

17:47.301 --> 17:50.836
Because we are moving
a lot of money around.

17:50.838 --> 17:53.305
There are tax implications.

17:53.307 --> 17:55.708
Also, I want to set things up
so whatever we earn,

17:55.710 --> 17:58.444
we share equally,
and we're protected

17:58.446 --> 18:01.447
if something were to go
wrong on one of our jobs.

18:01.449 --> 18:04.050
Anything the lawyer recommends,
I'll bring to all of us.

18:04.052 --> 18:06.585
We'll talk about it, discuss it.

18:06.587 --> 18:09.321
We'll decide together.
-Fine. We done?

18:09.323 --> 18:10.989
Where you going?
Work.

18:10.991 --> 18:13.992
Gotta go and sign some dead
people up for gym memberships.

18:13.994 --> 18:15.061
I gotta go, too.

18:15.063 --> 18:17.263
Look, J, I need you to pay this

18:17.265 --> 18:20.599
by the end of the week.

18:20.601 --> 18:22.134
What is it?

18:25.606 --> 18:27.673
18 grand?

18:27.675 --> 18:29.141
Pope, I thought we agreed --

18:29.143 --> 18:30.876
Just pay it.

18:30.878 --> 18:36.749
♪♪

18:36.751 --> 18:37.884
I, uh --

18:37.886 --> 18:39.886
I can't pay for this
with clean cash.

18:39.888 --> 18:43.489
I mean, paying it's a red flag
as it is.

18:43.491 --> 18:45.157
Yeah.

18:45.159 --> 18:47.760
Place is in Escondido --
maybe we can go grab

18:47.762 --> 18:49.495
a blank invoice,

18:49.497 --> 18:52.898
write in $1,000 instead
of $18,000 or something.

18:52.900 --> 18:54.900
Huh?

18:54.902 --> 18:58.905
Hit me up when you're done
with the lawyer shit, alright?

18:58.907 --> 19:00.606
Hey.

19:02.577 --> 19:04.510
You vouched for me
with Pope and Craig.

19:04.512 --> 19:06.312
Appreciate that.

19:06.314 --> 19:08.847
I'm gonna handle all of this.

19:08.849 --> 19:12.851
Just need a bit of time
and someone I can count on.

19:12.853 --> 19:15.253
Yeah.
I got you.

19:15.255 --> 19:16.722
Just don't mess it up.

19:16.724 --> 19:20.493
♪♪

19:25.266 --> 19:26.566
Hey.
My name's Josh Cody.

19:26.568 --> 19:29.034
I have an appointment.

19:29.036 --> 19:30.369
Someone will be right with you.

19:30.371 --> 19:31.904
Great.

19:31.906 --> 19:36.909
♪♪

19:36.911 --> 19:41.913
♪♪

19:41.915 --> 19:44.049
Mr Cody?

19:44.051 --> 19:45.651
Hi.
Hi. Penny Dean.

19:45.653 --> 19:47.586
Josh Cody.
Nice to meet you.

19:47.588 --> 19:50.389
Likewise. So, you're here for
an initial consultation

19:50.391 --> 19:52.391
regarding some
estate planning?

19:52.393 --> 19:54.794
Um, yeah, that's right.

19:54.796 --> 19:57.396
Great.

19:57.398 --> 19:59.531
I'm sorry.
You're an attorney?

19:59.533 --> 20:03.335
No.
Why do you ask?

20:03.337 --> 20:06.205
I handle a lot of our
initial consultations, Mr Cody.

20:06.207 --> 20:08.274
The partners here trust me --
so can you.

20:08.276 --> 20:11.143
Sorry -- did you get my message
about that thing?

20:11.145 --> 20:12.344
It's time sensitive.

20:12.346 --> 20:13.813
Yes, I responded.

20:13.815 --> 20:15.080
I didn't see it.

20:15.082 --> 20:16.549
It's there.

20:18.686 --> 20:20.352
Sorry about that.

20:20.354 --> 20:22.154
My job is to talk
to potential clients

20:22.156 --> 20:23.889
about their situation
and desired outcome

20:23.891 --> 20:26.558
to make sure they're fit
with the right attorney --

20:26.560 --> 20:28.694
one who can
work an e-mail.

20:28.696 --> 20:30.762
Fair enough.
Um...

20:30.764 --> 20:33.633
So, some family members
and I inherited

20:33.635 --> 20:36.902
a small portfolio
of properties.

20:36.904 --> 20:39.705
We're selling most of them
and buying small businesses,

20:39.707 --> 20:41.373
a couple of which
we've already got,

20:41.375 --> 20:44.176
but we're looking to consolidate
things as we buy more.

20:44.178 --> 20:45.511
All the businesses
in California?

20:45.513 --> 20:48.047
San Diego --
North County mostly.

20:48.049 --> 20:49.781
Not interested
in the real-estate game?

20:49.783 --> 20:54.786
No, I have an investment
strategy worked out.

20:54.788 --> 20:59.058
Okay. And, uh, the total dollar
value of the assets?

20:59.060 --> 21:00.992
Ballpark.

21:00.994 --> 21:04.930
$5 million, ballpark.

21:04.932 --> 21:06.932
Excellent.

21:06.934 --> 21:08.467
Uh, there'll be some forms
you have to sign,

21:08.469 --> 21:10.536
fee engagement,
letter of intent.

21:10.538 --> 21:12.672
I'll, uh -- I'll get them
and be right back.

21:12.674 --> 21:14.473
Thank you.

21:14.475 --> 21:17.310
And I'm sorry about
the attorney thing.

21:19.947 --> 21:21.747
I'll get those forms.

21:21.749 --> 21:27.152
♪♪

21:27.154 --> 21:30.690
[ Muffled singing ]

21:30.692 --> 21:33.959
Unplug it
and plug it back in.

21:33.961 --> 21:35.695
I did that.

21:35.697 --> 21:38.564
Can you do it again, please?

21:38.566 --> 21:41.833
I left the sales rep a message,
but I haven't heard back yet.

21:41.835 --> 21:43.903
[ Beeping ]

21:43.905 --> 21:45.571
You know, I don't even
understand why the hell we have

21:45.573 --> 21:47.039
these things.

21:47.041 --> 21:50.042
It's California, you can just
go for a run outside.

21:50.044 --> 21:51.310
People use them.

21:51.312 --> 21:53.312
Yeah, well,
people are idiots.

21:53.314 --> 21:54.780
Hi!
Welcome.

21:54.782 --> 21:57.383
You ready to change
your life today?

21:57.385 --> 22:00.586
Who bike is that?

22:00.588 --> 22:02.187
Mine.
Why?

22:02.189 --> 22:04.189
I'll call the rep again.

22:04.191 --> 22:06.392
Know those things'll
kill you, right?

22:06.394 --> 22:08.327
Yo', man, I'm busy.
What's up?

22:08.329 --> 22:10.529
Hey, that's a nice bike, man.

22:10.531 --> 22:12.398
Who built it?
A friend.

22:12.400 --> 22:14.734
Oh, is that right?
He from around here?

22:14.736 --> 22:17.136
No, Oceanside.

22:17.138 --> 22:19.238
Friend does nice work.

22:20.542 --> 22:23.743
Got to use better fuel
in it, though.

22:23.745 --> 22:25.344
She runs just fine, man.

22:25.346 --> 22:27.413
Got a lot of buildup
in the exhaust.

22:29.817 --> 22:32.752
Hey, look, man, I got a shop
down the street.

22:32.754 --> 22:35.955
Six mechanics,
two full-time welders,

22:35.957 --> 22:37.889
all custom fabrication.

22:37.891 --> 22:39.291
Bikes only.

22:39.293 --> 22:40.560
Bikes only?

22:40.562 --> 22:44.096
Bikes only.

22:44.098 --> 22:45.631
This your spot?

22:45.633 --> 22:46.966
Yeah.

22:46.968 --> 22:50.636
She's all mine.

22:50.638 --> 22:51.971
Hey, not bad.

22:51.973 --> 22:55.240
Yeah, appreciate that.

22:55.242 --> 22:57.843
Hey, look, bring your bike
by sometime.

22:57.845 --> 22:59.845
Yeah?
Yeah.

22:59.847 --> 23:03.849
You got a minute,
take a listen now.

23:03.851 --> 23:05.918
Yeah, alright.

23:05.920 --> 23:07.453
Alright.

23:07.455 --> 23:11.524
[ Revving engine ]

23:14.328 --> 23:16.328
Bike's great.

23:16.330 --> 23:17.997
Fuel's shitty.

23:17.999 --> 23:19.465
Ethanol.

23:19.467 --> 23:21.533
You need to be running
top-tier in this.

23:21.535 --> 23:22.401
Yeah?
What do you ride?

23:22.403 --> 23:23.803
Right now? Heh...

23:23.805 --> 23:25.137
Custom Springer.

23:25.139 --> 23:27.206
Custom Springer?

23:27.208 --> 23:28.941
How much you put into that?

23:28.943 --> 23:30.142
80 to 100 grand.

23:30.144 --> 23:31.511
That's a lot.

23:33.815 --> 23:36.682
Got clean six years ago.

23:36.684 --> 23:38.618
Couldn't believe
how much money I had.

23:38.620 --> 23:40.752
Yeah, man,
I just got clean, too.

23:40.754 --> 23:43.823
Only been a few months, though,
but, uh...

23:43.825 --> 23:46.626
that shit's hard, man,
you know?

23:46.628 --> 23:49.228
Think about how much
you miss it,

23:49.230 --> 23:52.097
all the fun you had,
you go right back.

23:52.099 --> 23:53.765
You got to find ways
to scratch that itch.

23:53.767 --> 23:55.701
Mm.
Know what I'm saying?

23:55.703 --> 23:58.904
Yeah, man.

23:58.906 --> 24:00.706
Hey, uh...

24:00.708 --> 24:03.643
why don't we go
for a ride?

24:03.645 --> 24:05.377
I'll take this,
feel her out,

24:05.379 --> 24:07.779
you take the Springer.

24:07.781 --> 24:08.648
[ Scoffs ]

24:08.650 --> 24:10.516
You're gonna let me ride
your custom?

24:10.518 --> 24:12.051
Unless you don't want to?
No, man, I'm in.

24:12.053 --> 24:14.053
Hey, if you're good,
I'm good.

24:14.055 --> 24:15.987
[ Chuckles ]
Let's go.

24:15.989 --> 24:22.994
♪♪

24:22.996 --> 24:27.333
♪♪

24:27.335 --> 24:30.002
[ Tires squealing ]

24:30.004 --> 24:31.871
Hey, asshole!

24:31.873 --> 24:37.009
♪♪

24:37.011 --> 24:38.944
Hey!

24:38.946 --> 24:46.418
♪♪

24:46.420 --> 24:47.687
You piece of shit!

24:47.689 --> 24:49.221
I'm sorry. I'm sorry!
You stealing from me?

24:49.223 --> 24:50.489
Sorry!
I'm sorry!

24:50.491 --> 24:51.957
I'm gonna kill you!

24:51.959 --> 24:53.959
I'm sorry, man!
I'm outta work!

24:53.961 --> 24:55.827
I'm outta work, man!
Please, I'm outta work!

24:55.829 --> 24:57.429
Nobody will hire me
if I ain't got tools, man!

24:57.431 --> 24:59.699
Please!
I'm a carpenter, bro!

24:59.701 --> 25:01.166
Come on.

25:01.168 --> 25:02.834
♪♪

25:02.836 --> 25:05.771
Wait.
You're a carpenter?

25:05.773 --> 25:07.507
Yeah.

25:07.509 --> 25:09.441
You know how to use those tools?
Yeah!

25:09.443 --> 25:12.778
That's why I was takin' 'em,
man, yeah.

25:12.780 --> 25:14.446
Alright, you got a choice.

25:14.448 --> 25:17.717
I kick your ass and you leave,
or you stay and help me out.

25:17.719 --> 25:20.586
But you -- you already
kicked my ass, man.

25:20.588 --> 25:21.987
Okay, okay!
Okay, okay!

25:21.989 --> 25:24.189
I'll help you!
Please, please, please.

25:24.191 --> 25:25.791
Alright, I'll help you, man.

25:28.996 --> 25:30.862
Let's go.

25:30.864 --> 25:36.802
♪♪

25:36.804 --> 25:38.870
How'd the meeting
with the lawyer go?

25:38.872 --> 25:41.540
Good. Yeah, I should check out
a couple more,

25:41.542 --> 25:43.142
due diligence.

25:43.144 --> 25:45.210
Yeah.

25:45.212 --> 25:47.212
It's pretty quiet, huh?

25:47.214 --> 25:50.149
Yeah, there's probably only one
or two people

25:50.151 --> 25:52.484
workin' in there at a time.

25:52.486 --> 25:54.553
Should be pretty easy.

25:54.555 --> 25:55.955
[ Dog barking ]

25:55.957 --> 25:58.290
You get in there,
you make a distraction,

25:58.292 --> 26:00.025
I'll find an invoice.

26:00.027 --> 26:01.861
Sounds good.

26:05.166 --> 26:07.232
Is that the owner?

26:07.234 --> 26:10.236
I don't know.
Looks like it.

26:10.238 --> 26:14.173
Why?
Do you know him?

26:14.175 --> 26:17.176
Yeah, uh...

26:17.178 --> 26:18.778
Let's come back later.

26:18.780 --> 26:20.646
Dude, no, we're here.
Let's just do this.

26:20.648 --> 26:22.914
No, no, come on.
I'll handle it later.

26:22.916 --> 26:25.885
♪♪

26:29.857 --> 26:38.363
♪♪

26:38.365 --> 26:46.972
♪♪

26:46.974 --> 26:50.375
♪ Breathe it in,
all the madness around you ♪

26:50.377 --> 26:53.779
♪ Feelin' like it's
the end of days ♪

26:53.781 --> 26:57.316
♪ Thrown aside, now you know
that you want to ♪

26:57.318 --> 27:00.919
♪ They don't know
better anyway ♪

27:00.921 --> 27:03.456
♪ Yeah ♪

27:03.458 --> 27:07.259
♪ Everybody's goin' crazy ♪

27:07.261 --> 27:10.529
♪ Yeah ♪

27:10.531 --> 27:13.999
♪ Don't you look away ♪

27:14.001 --> 27:17.602
♪ Yeah ♪

27:17.604 --> 27:21.006
♪ Everybody's goin' crazy ♪

27:21.008 --> 27:24.209
♪♪

27:24.211 --> 27:25.210
[ Engines turned off ]

27:25.212 --> 27:26.879
[ Chuckles ]

27:26.881 --> 27:30.415
[ Groans ]

27:30.417 --> 27:32.685
You win.

27:32.687 --> 27:36.489
Well, I had the better bike.

27:36.491 --> 27:37.956
No, bro, you can ride.

27:37.958 --> 27:39.091
Straight up.

27:39.093 --> 27:40.626
Yeah, well,

27:40.628 --> 27:43.762
I like to go fast.

27:43.764 --> 27:45.364
Guess that explains
all the blow.

27:45.366 --> 27:47.232
Same here.

27:47.234 --> 27:48.901
Now it's just bikes and women.

27:48.903 --> 27:51.404
And whatever other trouble
I can get into.

27:55.776 --> 27:57.376
You know, when I got clean,

27:57.378 --> 28:00.579
I went nuts.

28:00.581 --> 28:02.448
Looking for
any kind of thrill.

28:04.585 --> 28:09.388
Me and this guy,
just sober, we, uh --

28:09.390 --> 28:11.991
we hit the cellphone place.

28:11.993 --> 28:15.460
It was a strip mall
right off the freeway.

28:15.462 --> 28:17.930
Easy.
In and out.

28:17.932 --> 28:21.934
Wait a couple of minutes
before closing, boom.

28:24.339 --> 28:27.606
It was dumb.

28:27.608 --> 28:29.408
But it scratched that itch.

28:33.948 --> 28:38.483
Alright, man, well, look,
let's, uh, switch bikes,

28:38.485 --> 28:41.220
get some food,
and head back.

28:41.222 --> 28:42.821
I'm with that.
Yeah?

28:42.823 --> 28:44.023
Yeah.

28:44.025 --> 28:45.558
Alright.

28:45.560 --> 28:53.065
♪♪

29:07.648 --> 29:11.584
Pull it apart and do it again.

29:11.586 --> 29:12.585
What?
How come?

29:12.587 --> 29:13.786
Because none of it is flush.

29:13.788 --> 29:16.455
You got goddamn shiners.

29:18.593 --> 29:20.459
We're framing, bro.
We're not building a piano.

29:20.461 --> 29:23.596
Pull it apart...
and do it right.

29:25.933 --> 29:27.466
Do it right?

29:27.468 --> 29:30.069
You got nothing laid out, bro.

29:30.071 --> 29:31.871
What the hell are we even
working on, man?

29:36.343 --> 29:38.477
You know what?

29:38.479 --> 29:40.613
Kick my ass, whatever, man.

29:40.615 --> 29:42.481
I'm over this shit.

29:42.483 --> 29:45.284
You want me to work?
You got to pay me.

29:45.286 --> 29:46.685
Well, you ain't worth much.

29:46.687 --> 29:47.887
Yeah.
Yeah.

29:47.889 --> 29:49.688
Well, let me see hold
one end of the board

29:49.690 --> 29:51.490
and cut the other end.

29:53.628 --> 29:55.027
Shit...

29:55.029 --> 30:01.500
♪♪

30:01.502 --> 30:04.236
Fine -- 12 bucks an hour.

30:04.238 --> 30:06.238
Dudes at Home Depot are gonna
charge you $20, bro.

30:06.240 --> 30:10.443
Yep, 'cause they can nail shit
together flush.

30:10.445 --> 30:13.912
$18.
$15.

30:13.914 --> 30:17.049
Oh, you wanted to work.
This is work, man.

30:17.051 --> 30:19.584
Plus, you're using
my goddamn tools.

30:19.586 --> 30:26.058
♪♪

30:26.060 --> 30:27.326
Alright, $15.

30:27.328 --> 30:28.661
Cash, end of day, though,

30:28.663 --> 30:31.196
and I don't come in
before 8:30.

30:31.198 --> 30:32.765
We start at 8:00.

30:36.604 --> 30:38.337
Now pull it apart!

30:38.339 --> 30:40.273
Take off that stupid wool cap!

30:40.275 --> 30:43.476
It's 90 degrees!
It makes me sick to my stomach!

30:43.478 --> 30:44.943
♪♪

30:44.945 --> 30:49.748
[ Cheering, excited chatter
on television ]

30:49.750 --> 30:53.352
Mr. Cody,
I'm so sorry.

30:53.354 --> 30:54.620
It's not a problem.

30:54.622 --> 30:57.623
Just here and here,
both copies, please.

30:57.625 --> 31:01.294
And, uh, here you go.

31:01.296 --> 31:02.695
I could've come back,
you know.

31:02.697 --> 31:04.429
No, it was my fault.

31:04.431 --> 31:05.831
Besides, the office
was closing.

31:05.833 --> 31:08.100
This was on my way home.
I'm embarrassed.

31:08.102 --> 31:11.971
I-I've never missed
a signature before.

31:11.973 --> 31:13.506
Would you like to take a seat?

31:13.508 --> 31:17.109
The least I could offer you
is a -- is a drink.

31:17.111 --> 31:19.979
I mean, if --
if you're not in a hurry.

31:19.981 --> 31:21.580
Uh, no.

31:21.582 --> 31:22.982
It's just --
You know what?

31:22.984 --> 31:26.651
Yeah, sure.
What the hell?

31:26.653 --> 31:27.920
Could my friend get a drink,
please?

31:27.922 --> 31:29.454
Yeah, sure.
What can I get you?

31:29.456 --> 31:30.589
Uh, how's your margarita?

31:30.591 --> 31:33.326
Big.
Perfect.

31:33.328 --> 31:34.459
Long day?

31:34.461 --> 31:35.528
Yeah, they all are.

31:35.530 --> 31:37.596
Hmm.

31:37.598 --> 31:40.265
So, um, did you
grow up around here?

31:40.267 --> 31:41.666
No, Texas.

31:41.668 --> 31:43.202
My husband's active duty
out of Pendleton.

31:43.204 --> 31:45.470
Oh, I'm sorry.
I didn't see your ring.

31:45.472 --> 31:46.605
It's kind of hard to miss.

31:46.607 --> 31:48.273
[ Chuckles ]

31:48.275 --> 31:49.808
It's nice.

31:49.810 --> 31:51.076
It's just a CZ.

31:51.078 --> 31:52.611
My husband wanted me to wear
something bigger

31:52.613 --> 31:53.746
when he was away.

31:53.748 --> 31:54.947
He's deployed.

31:54.949 --> 31:56.749
Korea.

31:56.751 --> 31:58.483
That must be stressful.

31:58.485 --> 32:00.285
Force readiness training,
so no combat,

32:00.287 --> 32:01.687
but, yeah, stressful.

32:01.689 --> 32:05.290
Thank you.

32:05.292 --> 32:07.092
You miss him?

32:07.094 --> 32:08.961
♪♪

32:08.963 --> 32:10.763
Yes.

32:10.765 --> 32:12.297
If this is uncomfortable
for you,

32:12.299 --> 32:14.633
we can skip the drinks,
stick to the paperwork.

32:14.635 --> 32:17.703
Oh, no.
I'm allowed to have friends.

32:18.773 --> 32:20.839
Good.
Well...

32:20.841 --> 32:22.641
to new friends.

32:22.643 --> 32:24.243
Cheers.

32:24.245 --> 32:27.179
♪♪

32:27.181 --> 32:30.649
Mm.
Man, can you believe Smurf?

32:30.651 --> 32:32.317
We're all expelled from school,

32:32.319 --> 32:35.120
Andrew's got 60 hours
of community service,

32:35.122 --> 32:36.855
and now she's
throwing herself a party.

32:36.857 --> 32:38.991
Yeah, well, the party's
for Andrew.

32:38.993 --> 32:40.993
Yeah.
'Cause he loves parties.

32:40.995 --> 32:44.529
Hey, it's better
than juvie.

32:44.531 --> 32:46.932
[ Sighs ]
Whatever.

32:46.934 --> 32:48.668
I'm sick of her shit.

32:52.073 --> 32:56.541
Well, it's probably good
for Andrew, though, right?

32:56.543 --> 32:58.611
What?
Come on.

32:58.613 --> 33:01.747
You know how he gets.

33:01.749 --> 33:03.549
No, tell me --
how does he get?

33:05.486 --> 33:07.220
Hey, I'm just saying,
maybe Smurf is trying

33:07.222 --> 33:10.289
to look out for him.

33:10.291 --> 33:12.024
Awesome.

33:12.026 --> 33:14.560
So you're both sucked in
by her bullshit.

33:19.500 --> 33:26.639
♪♪

33:26.641 --> 33:33.846
♪♪

33:33.848 --> 33:42.855
♪♪

33:42.857 --> 33:46.859
You know, she took me in off
the street, right?

33:46.861 --> 33:48.861
And I'm sorry
for being grateful.

33:48.863 --> 33:53.799
♪♪

33:53.801 --> 33:56.535
Fine, okay?
One more, huh?

33:56.537 --> 33:58.270
Mellow you out.

33:58.272 --> 34:03.075
♪♪

34:03.077 --> 34:06.145
Ugh!

34:06.147 --> 34:08.147
Oh, man.

34:10.751 --> 34:12.952
So, you gonna get naked
in the pool again?

34:12.954 --> 34:16.221
Yeah, not happening.

34:16.223 --> 34:18.157
Well, maybe if I get you
wet first, you will.

34:18.159 --> 34:20.625
Baz!
Stop it, you perv.

34:20.627 --> 34:27.632
♪♪

34:27.634 --> 34:29.034
Come on.

34:29.036 --> 34:32.571
Smurf said to clean the place
up for the party.

34:32.573 --> 34:35.107
No.
Really?

34:35.109 --> 34:38.577
You're gonna sit there
and watch me?

34:38.579 --> 34:42.447
No, I'm gonna sit here...

34:42.449 --> 34:44.449
do acid, and watch you.

34:44.451 --> 34:48.254
♪♪

34:51.726 --> 34:53.058
We're closed.

34:53.060 --> 34:54.827
Open tomorrow at 7:00.

34:58.866 --> 35:00.933
I said we're closed.

35:00.935 --> 35:03.002
You remember me?

35:03.004 --> 35:05.338
No.
Should I?

35:05.340 --> 35:06.672
You're Brian, right?

35:06.674 --> 35:09.742
You, uh, run the amateur surf
competitions around here?

35:09.744 --> 35:11.010
Yeah.
Why?

35:11.012 --> 35:12.878
Were you a competitor?

35:12.880 --> 35:16.081
Maybe you remember
my mom.

35:16.083 --> 35:17.750
Yeah, there weren't a lot
of them handing you cash

35:17.752 --> 35:21.486
so their kid
would lose heats.

35:21.488 --> 35:23.956
Jesus.

35:23.958 --> 35:26.225
You're Smurf's kid.

35:26.227 --> 35:28.894
Danny, right?
No, Deran.

35:28.896 --> 35:31.030
Deran.

35:31.032 --> 35:33.799
Shit.
Uh, how's your mom doing?

35:35.370 --> 35:36.902
She's dead.

35:36.904 --> 35:40.773
[ Taser discharging ]

35:40.775 --> 35:42.375
Ah, Jesus!

35:42.377 --> 35:45.177
What was it, a hundred?
Two hundred?

35:45.179 --> 35:47.713
Is that what it was worth
to you?

35:47.715 --> 35:48.914
Look, it was a long time --

35:48.916 --> 35:50.783
[ Charges, discharges ]

35:50.785 --> 35:52.117
[ Groaning ]

35:52.119 --> 35:55.320
[ Gasping ]

35:55.322 --> 35:56.722
Sorry!

35:56.724 --> 35:58.857
I --

35:58.859 --> 36:02.595
I was scared of her, man.

36:02.597 --> 36:04.463
Now you can be scared of me.

36:04.465 --> 36:08.533
♪♪

36:08.535 --> 36:11.304
[ Barking ]

36:19.547 --> 36:21.813
So, tell me somethin'.

36:21.815 --> 36:23.215
Wassup?

36:23.217 --> 36:25.017
How long you been a cop?

36:27.755 --> 36:29.088
That's what you think?

36:29.090 --> 36:30.990
That's what I think.

36:32.960 --> 36:35.995
So you been looking at me
sideways this whole time.

36:41.703 --> 36:42.935
You got a piece in there?

36:46.307 --> 36:47.306
Good.

36:47.308 --> 36:52.311
I'll grab the kitchen,
crowd control...

36:52.313 --> 36:53.312
you get the cash.

36:53.314 --> 36:57.049
Four minutes, in and out.

36:57.051 --> 36:59.385
You're full of shit.

36:59.387 --> 37:01.186
Kind of backed me into it,
Robin.

37:01.188 --> 37:08.260
♪♪

37:08.262 --> 37:09.461
Hey!
Get down!

37:09.463 --> 37:10.529
All you get your asses down!

37:10.531 --> 37:12.531
Hey!
Go to the cash register!

37:12.533 --> 37:14.466
Get that money!
Alright, everybody stay calm!

37:14.468 --> 37:16.868
I don't want to hurt nobody.

37:16.870 --> 37:19.671
Cash and valuables
on the table now!

37:19.673 --> 37:21.540
But I can't say that
for my buddy right there.

37:21.542 --> 37:23.475
Let's move -- cash!
Grab the wallets!

37:23.477 --> 37:26.078
And send all these nice
people to the DMV?

37:26.080 --> 37:27.747
Nah, man,
that'd be the real crime.

37:27.749 --> 37:29.215
Look at that --
my boy's a sweetheart.

37:29.217 --> 37:31.016
Be ready! Let's go! Cash!
Let's have it out!

37:31.018 --> 37:32.151
Let's go!

37:32.153 --> 37:34.086
Let's go!

37:34.088 --> 37:35.887
Hurry that shit up!

37:35.889 --> 37:37.356
I guess we done then.

37:37.358 --> 37:40.626
Take it easy, baby!

37:40.628 --> 37:41.827
Check it out.
What do you think?

37:41.829 --> 37:43.095
Yeah, looks good.

37:43.097 --> 37:44.296
Nice board.

37:44.298 --> 37:45.765
Yeah, it's a '76 Lightning Bolt.

37:45.767 --> 37:47.166
You heard of that?

37:47.168 --> 37:48.500
Uh, no.

37:48.502 --> 37:50.169
Well, google it.

37:52.774 --> 37:54.440
Where'd you get it?

37:54.442 --> 37:57.176
A buddy of mine
I did a favor for.

37:58.712 --> 38:01.781
There you go.
A thousand bucks, itemized.

38:01.783 --> 38:03.715
Think you can cover that?

38:03.717 --> 38:04.917
Oh.

38:04.919 --> 38:06.051
Yes.

38:06.053 --> 38:08.520
Thank you.

38:08.522 --> 38:12.024
That's great.
Good job.

38:13.795 --> 38:17.329
I'm worried about Pope, man.
Why? What's going on?

38:17.331 --> 38:18.664
I've pitched him businesses.

38:18.666 --> 38:21.267
He doesn't even want
to talk about it.

38:21.269 --> 38:23.469
Wouldn't have to do shit.
I'd do all the work for him.

38:23.471 --> 38:26.071
Then what's he need
18 grand worth of lumber for?

38:26.073 --> 38:27.740
No idea.

38:31.613 --> 38:33.145
You know, when Smurf
was still alive,

38:33.147 --> 38:35.547
she used to cover all this shit,
day in and day out.

38:35.549 --> 38:38.818
I mean, you saw it.
Mm.

38:38.820 --> 38:41.220
Think the guy could use
a little bit of a break.

38:41.222 --> 38:44.356
Think you can cover him
for a bit?

38:44.358 --> 38:46.225
Yeah, I can figure
something out.

38:48.095 --> 38:49.495
How's Craig?

38:49.497 --> 38:51.831
He's good.
He's grumpy.

38:51.833 --> 38:53.165
He seems pretty organized.

38:53.167 --> 38:54.566
Yeah, he came
in here earlier.

38:54.568 --> 38:57.503
Wanted to switch
houses with me.

38:57.505 --> 38:58.904
Why?
I don't know.

38:58.906 --> 39:00.306
I guess he thinks it'll
help him stay sober

39:00.308 --> 39:03.042
or some shit.

39:03.044 --> 39:07.779
Sober or not, though, Renn's
not gonna let him keep that kid.

39:07.781 --> 39:09.315
Nick.

39:12.119 --> 39:14.453
Yeah, Nick.

39:14.455 --> 39:15.721
Give him a couple months,
he'll be back in here,

39:15.723 --> 39:18.658
hitting the bottle,
promise you that.

39:18.660 --> 39:21.861
Thought he was doing
pretty good.

39:21.863 --> 39:24.330
I liked him better high.

39:24.332 --> 39:30.602
♪♪

39:30.604 --> 39:33.272
[ Indistinct chatter,
shouting, laughter ]

39:33.274 --> 39:42.014
♪♪

39:42.016 --> 39:50.556
♪♪

39:50.558 --> 39:51.623
Oh, baby.

39:51.625 --> 39:54.026
Baby, baby, baby,
Baz was looking for you.

39:54.028 --> 39:56.229
He wasn't
looking that hard.

39:58.099 --> 40:01.367
He's just
enjoying himself.

40:01.369 --> 40:05.037
You should, too.

40:05.039 --> 40:06.572
Where's Julia?

40:08.510 --> 40:10.443
Around here somewhere.

40:14.382 --> 40:15.847
Relax!

40:15.849 --> 40:17.316
Have some fun!

40:17.318 --> 40:20.119
Man: Hey-hey!

40:20.121 --> 40:26.125
♪♪

40:26.127 --> 40:27.859
[ Locked ]

40:27.861 --> 40:33.399
♪♪

40:33.401 --> 40:38.738
♪♪

40:38.740 --> 40:43.609
[ Muffled music and voices
from outside ]

40:46.013 --> 40:49.014
Hey.

40:49.016 --> 40:52.151
Figured it was you.

40:52.153 --> 40:54.486
Baz and Smurf are busy,
and nobody else knows

40:54.488 --> 40:56.088
where the key is.

40:56.090 --> 40:57.222
What are you doing?

40:57.224 --> 41:00.359
Frying.

41:00.361 --> 41:03.462
Avoiding all human contact.

41:06.367 --> 41:09.168
How's the party?

41:09.170 --> 41:10.369
Baz is having fun.

41:10.371 --> 41:12.338
Of course he is.

41:17.111 --> 41:18.644
Did you break your board?

41:23.117 --> 41:27.186
I know you hate her,
but sh-she takes care of us.

41:29.190 --> 41:31.524
God, you sound like Baz.

41:43.537 --> 41:46.506
You know why I think
she doesn't like you skating?

41:48.476 --> 41:50.877
Because it makes you happy.

41:53.881 --> 41:56.882
All she cares about
is herself

41:56.884 --> 41:58.350
and this house.

41:58.352 --> 41:59.919
Nothing else.

42:02.690 --> 42:04.957
There's nothing
wrong with you.

42:04.959 --> 42:06.626
Hey, look at me.

42:09.363 --> 42:11.964
There's nothing
wrong with you.

42:11.966 --> 42:13.899
Okay?

42:13.901 --> 42:15.234
Nothing.

42:15.236 --> 42:18.370
♪♪

42:18.372 --> 42:20.105
I love you.

42:20.107 --> 42:27.579
♪♪

42:27.581 --> 42:30.850
[ Door opens, closes ]

42:30.852 --> 42:39.191
♪♪

42:39.193 --> 42:47.799
♪♪

42:47.801 --> 42:56.141
♪♪

42:56.143 --> 43:04.684
♪♪

43:04.686 --> 43:13.092
♪♪

43:13.094 --> 43:21.633
♪♪

43:21.635 --> 43:24.503
[ Coughs ]
Whoa. Hey!

43:24.505 --> 43:26.438
Hey!
There's a fire!

43:26.440 --> 43:29.041
There's a fire in there!
What? Oh, shit!

43:29.043 --> 43:31.243
Shit! I got it.

43:31.245 --> 43:36.181
♪♪

43:36.183 --> 43:40.252
Shit!

43:40.254 --> 43:44.724
♪♪

43:44.726 --> 43:46.992
Don't kick it towards
the car!

43:46.994 --> 43:52.864
♪♪

43:52.866 --> 43:54.333
We need some air in here.

43:54.335 --> 43:55.401
Hey, it's okay.
Thank you.

43:55.403 --> 43:56.536
Guys, everybody out.

43:56.538 --> 43:58.137
You know, e-everyone out.

43:58.139 --> 43:59.004
Party's over.

43:59.006 --> 44:00.672
Come on, come on,
come on, come on!

44:00.674 --> 44:02.542
Out!
Out!

44:02.544 --> 44:04.143
Get -- Get --
No.

44:04.145 --> 44:06.212
Get. Come on.

44:06.214 --> 44:08.013
Go inside.

44:08.015 --> 44:16.222
♪♪

44:16.224 --> 44:24.630
♪♪

44:24.632 --> 44:32.972
♪♪

44:32.974 --> 44:41.380
♪♪

44:41.382 --> 44:49.789
♪♪

44:49.791 --> 44:58.197
♪♪

44:58.199 --> 45:06.538
♪♪

45:06.540 --> 45:14.746
♪♪

45:14.748 --> 45:16.682
Whoa!
[ Laughs ]

45:16.684 --> 45:24.390
♪♪

45:37.371 --> 45:45.044
♪♪

45:45.046 --> 45:52.652
♪♪

45:52.654 --> 46:00.726
♪♪
